title: Alice Cooper
description:
With a career span of over 5 decades the grand master of horror rock Alice Cooper made a huge impact on rock music. He was always in front never followed anyone just did what he wanted and let everyone try to copy him. From the 1969 release Pretties for You to the last one Dirty Diamonds Alice was always ahead of his time. The bands who tried to keep up with him are endless. Bands like Kiss, Twisted Sisters and WASP over to new bands like Marily Manson, NIN and Lordi are all under heavy influence by him. With songs like Schools Out, No More mr Nice Guy, Feed My Frankenstein, Poison, 18 he really deserved his place in the Rock And Roll Hall of Fame. 

Since this is the complete discography its a bit hard to find any bonuses but i managed to sneak in two. The first is the 1969 live rare live release of a Toronto show called Toronto rock 'n' roll revival and the second is all the covers to every record.
